@inherits BlogPost
@{
    Page.Title = "First Post";

    //For BlogPost, a Published date is required
    //Use the short form with a string or the full DateTime constructor.
    Page.Published = "2025-07-01";
    Page.Published = new DateTime(2025, 7, 1);

    //Tags: Comma separated
    Page.Tags = "first";
}

## Making a Blog post

<Summary Render>
    By using `@@inherits @(nameof(BlogPost))` the page will be included in the list of **posts and the feeds**.
</Summary>

<MyUpdate Date="2025-07-03 12:00">
    This is an update to the post.
    It will generate a new item in the feed.
</MyUpdate>

<MyUpdate Date="2025-07-05 12:00" Render>
    This is another update.

    This one has the attribute `Render` which will make it appear in the post itself.
</MyUpdate>